phrases: I thought that if it was also using lightning to attack,
there would be an opening while it switched over.
Looks like it is not going to be that easy.
In which case, what are our other options...?
HQ has ordered us to pull out.
Dales and Orlov Platoons should have gotten the order by now.
That invisible Kataphraktos we failed to destroy is over there.
Clydesdale Leader to Orlov Leader, can you hear me?
I have done all I can.
The rest is up to her.
The smoke screen should obstruct the enemy's vision a little.
We can use this smoke to attack.
I thought you were going to keep Lightning busy!
Its fire suddenly shifted, like it was concentrating in your direction.
We are managing to discharge it!
Set us down and extract all Kataphraktoi.
That is right in the middle of the enemy!
You are descending too fast, and there is a strong tail wind!
The Aldnoah drive is handling it!
Same type as the one we just destroyed!
Another at our 2 of the clock!
Weather radar, Doppler radar, both offline!
Our discharge system must have been damaged by Invisibility's arrow.
GPS display lost, 2D radar also offline!
You are amenable to serving Count Troyard, then?
I shall pass word along at once.
There is one other favor I would ask of you.
Might I be granted an audience with Princess Asseylum?
A personal audience with Her Highness?
And if possible, with Count Troyard as well.
However, I will endeavor to see that you are accommodated.
It will come at a price.
I must say, defeat normally causes a man to lose his way, but not you.
Getting into the good graces of not only Count Troyard,
but Princess Asseylum as well, would be most beneficial.
However, do not wear your ambition on your sleeve.
There is a chance that it might trip you up.
Congratulations on your victory, Milord Slaine.
This is no because for celebration, not when the enemy escaped.
The objective of securing territory was accomplished.
This is sure to cause more knights to swear loyalty to you.
We cannot let our guard down.
Nothing is less reliable than a knight's vow of loyalty.
And about that request from Count Barouhcruz?
If he wants to see the princess, let him see her.
She is happily fulfilling her role of extending our power base.
For the time being, at least.
This goes way beyond a quick fix.
Night vision's also out, so I cannot even fly by eye.
How did you know, Lt. Kaizuka?
It is faint, but the fuselage is carrying a charge.
With this ship, engine-related malfunctions are unlikely.
We are all kinds of screwed!
You should lower our altitude a little.
Low enough to keep us off enemy radar.
But the altimeter and GPWS are both dead, so I am scared to take us too low.
I can tell how high we are.
Can you also pick up VOR stations?
Once you have both signals, tell me.
I was trying to put us on 110.
Fly at an offset of 3 degrees for 2 minutes.
Then straighten out and maintain heading.
Are we caught in some nasty turbulence?
It looks like it goes on for a while.
Just to be safe, you should...
From here on out, it looks like it is experience that is most important.
Once I pick up an LLG, I will let you know.
Actually, we should be thanking you for earlier.
Lt. Marito was pretty surprised that you would do something so crazy.
You are the last person I want to hear that from.
Preparations for the founding are proceeding smoothly, then?
I can hardly wait for this new kingdom.
And to be able to go to your homeworld.
It is a world inhabited by vulgar trash.
It is hardly the restful place conjured up by the word home.
Rather, I never had such a place to begin with.
There is nowhere that I might find solace,
neither on Vers or in royal standing.
Anywhere that I may be together with you,
more than anywhere else, that is my...
I shall call on you again later, then.
My apologies, but there are still pressing matters that I must attend to.
Nina was gushing about how you helped out.
What do you think about the enemy coordinating their actions?
Maybe they are so hard pressed that they have been forced to swallow their pride.
Judging from the outcome, I do not think we have much to fear.
Do you suppose it is connected to that proclamation, then?
That Orbital Knight named Slaine Troyard who is behind Princess Asseylum...
The way I hear it, he one-ups even Kaizuka Jr.
If this opponent really is setting things into motion with a goal in mind,
it is not a simple scheme that we can counter with just superior resources.
Launch all-out attack on captured territory and retake it.
That is the long and short of it.
And how have you been feeling since?
The very fact that you regained consciousness was a miracle.
Please do not force yourself to remember.
I am afraid that I must take my leave now.
I can guess what it is that you wish to ask.
Taking me as her husband and founding a country...
That proclamation issued by Princess Lemrina
was entirely the result of the weakness in my heart.
Princess Asseylum is sure to wake up.
I tried to hold on to that belief but failed, having given up somewhere deep down.
But then a miracle happened, as if to reprimand me for being such a fool.
With the situation having changed so drastically,
what I must think about now is, how can I make Her Highness happy?
As to what she is looking for...
The same thing as me, I suspect.
A place where she can find solace.
But that is something that neither of us will ever obtain.
We must not tell her everything yet.
But even if she looks down on or derides me for what I am doing here,
I had waited with such hope for Her Highness to awaken.
But now, what I hope for is that her memory never returns.
Your newfound resolve to serve my trusted Count Troyard
fills me with such joy that I cannot contain it.
I am fully prepared to serve both Your Highness
and Count Troyard with wholehearted devotion.
I, too, was touched by Count Mazuurek's drive
as he swore to rise up once again for the sake of Vers' future
even as he was held prisoner on Earth.
I am given to understand that you once underwent similar hardships on Earth.
Terrans are all such... vulgar trash.
There was not a single one that Your Highness grew close to?
I left all interaction with Terrans to my handmaiden.
I once entertained the notion of reconciling with those people,
but I now see what a fool I was.
Why is Slaine not here at a time like this?
Lord Slaine is rushing about, making preparations for the new operation.
He has been locking himself away in his castle far too often lately.
Whatever he is doing, can he not do it here?
I am told that precious resources are involved.
Then I shall go to him.
I shall go over to the Landing Castle.
Tell me, how long will it be...
I shall see you to your room, Highness.
Please pardon the delay, Count Mazuurek.
Please follow me to the parlor.
You seem to have finished checking my credentials.
Not at all, it is I who committed a grave blunder.
To think that my ship broke down...
How fortunate for me that you were in the vicinity.
Count Troyard is still at the moonbase.
I regret to say that you have missed him.
Lord Harklight is on his way here now.
I made my move as soon as I was certain that he was not here.
Troyard is commuting between here and the moonbase more than is necessary.
Meaning that the princess' location must be...
This castle has undergone quite the transformation.
I was an acquaintance of its former master.
He detested all things Terran, fearing that they harbored microorganisms.
There is no such worry here.
Oh, you have been to Earth, then?
N-No, that is only what I have heard.
I had heard that Princess Asseylum had an attendant, but I did not expect-
Her Highness went to Earth alone.
No one is speaking of Earth.
You truly have not gone there?
Do you know what happened on Earth?
What about a boy named Inaho Kaizuka?
How long will it be before you release your grip on his feelings?
He said that he wanted me to give it to you.
To the princess who knew about Earth.
